-- Egypt Planning a $10.5 Billion Upgrade of Irrigation Networks, Al Mal Says
-- Ola Galal
-- 2010-09-07T06:33:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-07/egypt-planning-a-10-5-billion-upgrade-of-irrigation-networks-al-mal-says.html

          
          
             Egypt plans to upgrade irrigation
networks covering 5 million feddans (5.19 million acres) of
agricultural land with an initial cost of 60 billion Egyptian
pounds ($10.5 billion),  Al Mal  reported, citing Agriculture
Minister  Amin Abaza.   
